Cody took a step. “Yep. Just a few more feet, and I'm sure I'll get somewhere. After all, this corridor can't be endless. There's no such thing as an endless corridor.” He slid forward another step. “Unless it's a magical corridor, and all part of the experiment.” He noticed, distantly, that his breathing was getting faster. He glanced behind, but he could no longer see Lulu, depriving him of even that questionable reassurance.
